parameters: Do you want to skip class?

I am Hoffman, the one in charge of curse magic
class.
We have gathered more than usual this year.

Curse magic isn't very popular, but I'm delighted
to see so many students interested in it.
Well then, let's get started with the class.

Curse magic refers to magic that is different from
regular magic, as it involves using tools or parts
of the human body.

I'm sure you know that there are mainly two types.
Amador, why don't you give it a try?
Yes, it's sympathetic magic and contagious magic.

That's right. Sympathetic magic utilizes the
principle that similar things can influence each
other.

For example, it's a magic that can cause harm to
both the person and the doll that resembles a
human form.

Contagious magic has the nature of affecting
things that have once come into contact or were
originally one, even if they are separated.

It's a magic that can affect the person by using
things like their hair or nails.
By the way, this also includes names.
That's why many wizards hide their real names.
Masamune, you've never studied magic, have you?

Because this class assumes that you've studied the
basics in your first year.
(What's wrong, Elena? Play with my dick!)
What's wrong? Why are you making a strange face?

No, it's nothing. Well, I understand the basics so
there shouldn't be any problems for now.

(Could it be that the events from the previous
loop are affecting me...)
(Maybe it's not just Amelia who's affected...)

Hiyo is from the same hometown, right? Please get
along with her.
Yes, nice to meet you too.
I believe it was the student council, right?
Yes, but... did you talk to her?
(I didn't know at this stage. I messed up...)
No, I heard it from Tommy.
Isn't it amazing to enter in just two years?

That's not true. I'm the only one in the student
council for two years, but it's just because
there's no one else who wants to be.

There are a lot of miscellaneous tasks, you know.
By any chance, Masamune-san, are you interested in
the student council?

However, I heard that this school doesn't have a
student council president, so I'm a little
curious.

Yes, that's right. When I joined, I also found it
strange.

However, it's just a tradition and doesn't have
any special meaning.
Hehe, you're an interesting person, aren't you?

If you're interested in the student council,
please let me know.

Oh, it's fine even if it's Professor Hoffman, the
advisor.

(So Professor Hoffman is also the advisor of the
student council...)

(If that's the case, I can also touch the
confiscated magic circle)

(It's still too early to doubt, but it's better to
keep it in mind)

I've become too close with a girl right after
transferring.
